Gordon Ewen captured the photograph using a telescope at the bottom of his garden in Letchworth, Hertfordshire . 
  The strange formation was photographed by amateur astronomer Gordon Ewen and is a sun spot . 
  They occur when a concentration of magnetic fields causes the surface temperature to reduce . 
  Sun spots range in size from 10 miles (16km) to 100,000 miles (160,000km) wide . 
 